  "prompt": "What are the disadvantages of being an only child?",
  "response": "Here are some potential disadvantages of being an only child:\n\n1. Social development challenges\n- Less practice with sibling interactions\n- May struggle with sharing and compromise\n- Potentially less experience with conflict resolution\n\n2. Emotional aspects\n- Can feel more pressure to meet parents' expectations\n- Might experience loneliness\n- Could feel more isolated during childhood\n\n3. Family dynamics\n- No built-in playmates at home\n- More intense parental focus and potential overprotection\n- Potentially more adult-like conversations early on\n\n4. Personal characteristics\n- May develop more self-centered tendencies\n- Could have difficulty adapting to group settings\n- Might have less practice with interpersonal skills\n\n5. Future responsibilities\n- Sole caregiver for aging parents\n- Full responsibility for family inheritance/estate management\n- More emotional burden during family challenges\n\n6. Psychological considerations\n- Higher likelihood of feeling different or unique\n- Potentially more sensitive to criticism\n- Could develop stronger dependency on parents\n\n7. Financial and practical matters\n- No sibling support system\n- No one to share family responsibilities\n- Potentially more financial burden for parents\n\nNote that these are generalizations, and individual experiences vary widely based on parenting, personality, and personal circumstances.",
